# Required Dependencies for Matching Components

To use the matching question components, ensure your project has the following dependencies installed:

## Core Dependencies

```json
{
  "dependencies": {
    "react": "^18.0.0 or higher",
    "@radix-ui/react-select": "^2.0.0 or higher"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "tailwindcss": "^3.0.0 or higher",
    "@types/react": "^18.0.0 or higher",
    "typescript": "^5.0.0 or higher"
  }
}
```

## Installation

Install the required packages:

```bash
# Install Radix UI Select
npm install @radix-ui/react-select

# Or with yarn
yarn add @radix-ui/react-select

# Or with pnpm
pnpm add @radix-ui/react-select
```

## Tailwind CSS Configuration

Ensure your Tailwind CSS configuration includes the necessary paths:

```javascript
// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  content: [
    "./src/**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}",
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {},
  },
  plugins: [],
}
```

## Radix UI Setup

Radix UI components are unstyled by default. These components use Tailwind CSS classes for styling.
No additional CSS imports are required beyond your Tailwind setup.

## TypeScript Support

These components are written in TypeScript and include type definitions. Ensure your project is configured for TypeScript:

```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "es5",
    "lib": ["dom", "dom.iterable", "esnext"],
    "allowJs": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "allowSyntheticDefaultImports": true,
    "strict": true,
    "forceConsistentCasingInFileNames": true,
    "noFallthroughCasesInSwitch": true,
    "module": "esnext",
    "moduleResolution": "node",
    "resolveJsonModule": true,
    "isolatedModules": true,
    "noEmit": true,
    "jsx": "react-jsx"
  },
  "include": ["src"]
}
```
